<TITLE> Four road accidents kill 5, injure at least 100 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 22 (bdnews24.com)  Five people died and 100 others were injured in four road accidents in Mymensingh, Pabna and Munsiganj districts Friday, the police said. A speeding bus slammed into a taxi cab in Trishal on Dhaka-Mymensingh highway, leaving two people dead and 10 others wounded. Trishal police chief Tarapod Shikdar said they could not identify the deceased immediately. He said three severely injured people were taken to Mymensingh Medical College and Hospital while the rest to a local health complex. In Pabna, two people were killed and at least 20 others injured in two road mishaps. Pabna police chief AFM Masud Rabbani said a Kushtia-bound bus lost its control and crushed a passerby before falling into a roadside ditch. The dead, identified as Sharmin Sarkar, 25, died instantly at the scene. At least 20 others were wounded in the incident. A young man, Tasif Uddin, died separately after two locally-made passenger carriers collided in the district's Bagchipara area. A passenger bus lost its control and fell into a roadside ditch on Dhaka-Mawa highway in Munshiganj amid driving rainfall, leaving one dead and at least 30 others injured. The injured were taken to different hospitals and clinics in the capital. Srinagar police chief Saidur Rahman said rescuers lifted the bus in the afternoon and found the body inside the wreckage, but his identity could not be immediately determined. Separately, a Dhaka-bound bus collided with a Mawa-bound bus on the same highway, leaving at least 40 people injured. Srinagar sub-inspector Mohammed Habib said they were trying to salvage one of the buses that fell into a roadside ditch. bdnews24.co
